U.K. Card Fraud Falls to Lowest Level in 10 Years, FT Reports

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-03-09T11:59:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/u-k-card-fraud-falls-to-lowest-level-in-10-years-ft-reports.html
U.K. credit- and debit-card fraud
fell to the lowest level in a decade last year, the Financial
Times reported, citing figures from the UK Cards Association and
Financial Fraud Action UK.  Total losses were 365.4 million pounds ($593 million), down
from 610 million pounds in 2008, when card crime reached a
record high, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Purkiss in  London  on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 